<div style="text-align:center"></div><div style="font-family:'Pacifico',sans-serif;background:-webkit-linear-gradient(90deg,#F3722C,#F94144);color:#d3d3d3;border:3px solid #ffffff;padding:5px 10px;margin:1em;text-align:center;"><font size="6">Colonies & Outposts</font></div>
'''Level 629''' is subject to the [[Phenomenon 15|Alone Phenomenon]], preventing multiple wanderers from entering the same instance of the level simultaneously, therefore making the creation of colonies or outposts impossible.

<div style="text-align:center"></div><div style="font-family:'Pacifico',sans-serif;background:-webkit-linear-gradient(90deg,#F3722C,#F94144);color:#d3d3d3;border:3px solid #ffffff;padding:5px 10px;margin:1em;text-align:center;"><font size="6">Entrances & Exits</font></div>
The most stable way to ingress Level 629 is entering fuschia doors with a sunset, but various others undocumented, unstable or non-listed ways to ingress Level 629 has been discovered for long periods of time.
----
There's only 4 known ways to egress Level 629;
*The main way used by travelers is by red waterslides within the households, that are rarely found, leading one to [[Level 30]];
*Random structures may lead one to [[Level 85]];
*Noclipping into the floor may lead you to [[Level 34]].

